1
00:00:08,979 --> 00:00:10,979
[insects chirping softly]

2
00:00:24,271 --> 00:00:26,271
[metal door rattling]

3
00:00:28,937 --> 00:00:30,312
[cat meows]

4
00:00:46,854 --> 00:00:48,354
[snaps fingers]

5
00:00:48,437 --> 00:00:50,437
["Tole Galva"
by Jkevlar, Tency & Titis playing]

6
00:01:07,812 --> 00:01:09,812
[upbeat rap song continues]

7
00:01:46,104 --> 00:01:48,062
[song fades]

8
00:01:49,854 --> 00:01:51,354
Let's get out of here.

9
00:01:54,979 --> 00:01:57,604
- It's a bust.
- Come on, that's nothing. We got this.

10
00:01:57,687 --> 00:01:59,812
You have no idea what's even in there.
Drop it.

11
00:01:59,896 --> 00:02:02,354
I'll tell you what's there.
Full tank of gas.

12
00:02:02,437 --> 00:02:04,896
And that fancy-ass buggy
for your son, bro.

13
00:02:04,979 --> 00:02:07,271
You ain't fed up carrying him around
in that baby sling?

14
00:02:07,354 --> 00:02:08,479
He ain't a bag of potatoes!

15
00:02:23,062 --> 00:02:23,896
There's nothing.

16
00:02:25,062 --> 00:02:26,062
You check the old boxes?

17
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:29,854
[man on intercom] Hey,
you fucking masked assholes!

18
00:02:30,437 --> 00:02:31,354
Get out of here!

19
00:02:32,729 --> 00:02:35,771
- Let's go!
- Hell no! We still got five minutes.

20
00:02:35,854 --> 00:02:38,687
[man] You steal from Milord, you're dead.

21
00:02:38,771 --> 00:02:39,896
"Milord"?

22
00:02:40,812 --> 00:02:42,812
[expectant music playing]

23
00:03:26,312 --> 00:03:27,854
Fuck you, Milord!

24
00:03:28,354 --> 00:03:31,146
BEREKYA GROCERY

25
00:03:34,896 --> 00:03:37,854
[man] You see?
The bastards took everything!

26
00:03:37,937 --> 00:03:39,729
That's why I can't pay you.

27
00:03:40,979 --> 00:03:41,979
How much?

28
00:03:42,062 --> 00:03:45,104
I don't know, around 2K and some product.

29
00:03:45,854 --> 00:03:50,021
2K, some product,
locked up with only a bike lock?

30
00:03:50,104 --> 00:03:51,396
It's not that--

31
00:03:57,604 --> 00:03:58,937
Fuck you, Milord!

32
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:04,854
I'll give you two more weeks,
but with interest.

33
00:04:09,979 --> 00:04:11,021
Milord?

34
00:04:13,187 --> 00:04:14,437
I need a refill.

35
00:04:17,771 --> 00:04:19,646
[man] What should we do
about your brother?

36
00:04:19,729 --> 00:04:24,562
It's happened a few times now.
If we let him slide, we lose credibility.

37
00:04:24,646 --> 00:04:27,271
We're not letting him slide,
but I gotta be sure.

38
00:04:28,646 --> 00:04:30,646
[darkly intriguing music playing]

39
00:04:30,729 --> 00:04:33,062
[sighs] Fuck.

40
00:04:34,146 --> 00:04:37,146
[darkly intriguing music continues]

41
00:05:05,812 --> 00:05:07,812
[women chatting and laughing]

42
00:05:14,104 --> 00:05:16,104
[drone buzzing]

43
00:05:19,646 --> 00:05:20,979
The hell is that?

44
00:05:27,854 --> 00:05:30,854
[upbeat music playing in background]

45
00:05:39,437 --> 00:05:41,437
[upbeat music playing loudly]

46
00:05:43,021 --> 00:05:43,979
Hey!

47
00:05:44,062 --> 00:05:45,812
- [man 1] Hooray!
- [man 2] Happy birthday!

48
00:05:45,896 --> 00:05:47,187
[woman 1] Happy birthday, Kiki!

49
00:05:47,271 --> 00:05:48,521
[man 3] Happy birthday, dawg!

50
00:05:48,604 --> 00:05:51,437
- [woman 2] Here he is! Birthday boy!
- [man 4] Yo, man! Come get a drink!

51
00:05:51,521 --> 00:05:54,021
- [man 5] Happy birthday, my man.
- [woman 3] Happy birthday!

52
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:55,479
Looking cool.

53
00:05:57,146 --> 00:06:00,062
What up, Fatso? Like your present?

54
00:06:00,146 --> 00:06:02,271
- What, the drone?
- Hell yeah, dawg!

55
00:06:05,271 --> 00:06:07,229
Hey, Marvin's got something to show you.

56
00:06:07,312 --> 00:06:11,271
[woman] Hey! Happy birthday,
my favorite little brother!

57
00:06:12,021 --> 00:06:14,562
So the big day is finally here. [laughing]

58
00:06:18,771 --> 00:06:22,521
Happy birthday, bro.
You're late. Where were you?

59
00:06:22,604 --> 00:06:24,021
[Kylian] Uh, I got detention.

60
00:06:24,104 --> 00:06:26,354
Even on your birthday, you got detention?

61
00:06:26,437 --> 00:06:28,396
Damn history teacher hates my guts.

62
00:06:28,979 --> 00:06:31,271
- Have a seat.
- [upbeat music continues]

63
00:06:38,312 --> 00:06:39,354
How old are you?

64
00:06:41,187 --> 00:06:42,312
Sixteen.

65
00:06:42,396 --> 00:06:43,604
[Marvin] Sixteen!

66
00:06:45,104 --> 00:06:46,562
You know what that means?

67
00:07:08,562 --> 00:07:10,146
[Marvin] It's a lotus flower.

68
00:07:11,396 --> 00:07:12,729
It symbolizes purity.

69
00:07:12,812 --> 00:07:14,604
All things good.

70
00:07:16,146 --> 00:07:17,562
The Lafleur family ring.

71
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:19,646
[emotional music playing]

72
00:07:28,854 --> 00:07:32,979
So, anyway, it's open bar tonight.
Go get something.

73
00:07:33,521 --> 00:07:34,729
And bring the champagne!

74
00:07:35,521 --> 00:07:37,354
King, can I talk to you a minute?

75
00:07:37,437 --> 00:07:38,521
Let's go.

76
00:07:46,937 --> 00:07:48,271
Where'd you get the drone?

77
00:07:48,979 --> 00:07:50,104
I pulled in favors.

78
00:07:51,896 --> 00:07:53,229
The party was also favors?

79
00:07:53,812 --> 00:07:55,687
Man, what's with the questions?

80
00:07:55,771 --> 00:07:57,312
Tell me it was legit.

81
00:07:57,812 --> 00:07:58,937
Yeah?

82
00:07:59,021 --> 00:08:01,437
When it's for the family,
everything's legit.

83
00:08:01,521 --> 00:08:03,312
Don't mean it's not insane.

84
00:08:04,312 --> 00:08:05,812
Come on, bruh!

85
00:08:06,437 --> 00:08:08,812
It's your birthday, chill out a bit.

86
00:08:09,396 --> 00:08:12,021
Just because you're
on that purity ring bullshit

87
00:08:12,104 --> 00:08:13,979
don't mean you get to jerk me around.

88
00:08:14,771 --> 00:08:16,229
Go have fun, man.

89
00:08:19,479 --> 00:08:23,729
Yo! So I lost
a bet to my brother, Kingsley.

90
00:08:23,812 --> 00:08:26,812
So I've got for you a bit of freestyle.

91
00:08:27,687 --> 00:08:31,646
Since I'm embarrassing myself already,
might as well embarrass my brother too.

92
00:08:31,729 --> 00:08:35,021
Chain reaction.
Go take it out on King, he's expecting it.

93
00:08:35,687 --> 00:08:38,062
Lafleur is the flame.

94
00:08:38,146 --> 00:08:40,771
[upbeat rap song playing]

95
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:42,729
♪ First verse
Things about to pop off ♪

96
00:08:42,812 --> 00:08:44,854
♪ Open your ears wide
I dedicate these lines to you ♪

97
00:08:44,937 --> 00:08:46,979
♪ It comes from the heart
Big love for you ♪

98
00:08:47,062 --> 00:08:49,062
♪ Long life to you
You're on my radar ♪

99
00:08:49,146 --> 00:08:51,229
♪ Bound by blood
This life, there are no coincidences ♪

100
00:08:51,312 --> 00:08:53,396
[freestyling continues in background]

101
00:08:54,146 --> 00:08:55,146
IT WAS KING

102
00:08:57,354 --> 00:09:01,354
IT WAS KING. DO IT AT DAWN. NO HOSPITAL.

103
00:09:01,437 --> 00:09:03,979
[all] ♪ Lafleur is the flame ♪

104
00:09:04,062 --> 00:09:06,104
[all] ♪ Siblings are in the soul ♪

105
00:09:06,187 --> 00:09:08,187
♪ Lafleur is the flame
All bound by the heart ♪

106
00:09:08,271 --> 00:09:10,312
[all] ♪ Ain't no stopping it

107
00:09:10,396 --> 00:09:13,312
[freestyling continues]

108
00:09:17,687 --> 00:09:20,937
- [freestyling fades into background]
- [emotional music playing]

109
00:09:43,562 --> 00:09:46,021
[man] King. King.

110
00:09:46,104 --> 00:09:48,437
- [Kingsley groans]
- There's a guy here for you.

111
00:10:07,979 --> 00:10:08,979
Yo.

112
00:10:09,062 --> 00:10:11,479
- I'm hearing you got some party favors.
- [sighs]

113
00:10:11,562 --> 00:10:14,271
The time for fun is over, brother.
Go home, okay?

114
00:10:14,354 --> 00:10:17,646
I have a bud who wants seven bills
worth of dope, it's easy money.

115
00:10:18,396 --> 00:10:19,396
Where is he?

116
00:10:19,479 --> 00:10:20,687
Down below.

117
00:10:23,187 --> 00:10:24,354
Bring me to him.

118
00:10:37,646 --> 00:10:38,771
This your guy?

119
00:10:40,562 --> 00:10:41,562
So dope goes for--

120
00:10:41,646 --> 00:10:43,979
Ahh! The fuck your problem?

121
00:10:44,062 --> 00:10:45,104
[grunts]

122
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:47,271
That's from Milord.

123
00:10:47,354 --> 00:10:50,771
- ["Yo pa Méchan" by Shannon playing]
- [groaning]

124
00:11:00,271 --> 00:11:02,271
[song continues in background]

125
00:11:03,021 --> 00:11:05,021
Annabelle's still not answering her phone.

126
00:11:05,104 --> 00:11:08,812
That girl's gonna be the death of me.
We'll have to make a cake.

127
00:11:09,812 --> 00:11:11,312
I mean, I guess so.

128
00:11:12,562 --> 00:11:14,229
Mama!

129
00:11:17,729 --> 00:11:19,896
I made some plum juice for Ms. Janine.

130
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,312
[Mama] That's great.

131
00:11:21,896 --> 00:11:23,229
I brought in your groceries.

132
00:11:23,312 --> 00:11:24,729
Fantastic.

133
00:11:25,937 --> 00:11:27,187
Nolan?

134
00:11:28,312 --> 00:11:29,396
Nothing.

135
00:11:29,896 --> 00:11:31,354
The toilets.

136
00:11:43,187 --> 00:11:44,896
Marvin gave me this.

137
00:11:49,104 --> 00:11:51,104
[song fading]

138
00:12:03,104 --> 00:12:04,646
Whoa, is this real?

139
00:12:04,729 --> 00:12:05,896
A Glock 19.

140
00:12:06,479 --> 00:12:07,521
This is Mama's, isn't it?

141
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:11,104
You've lost your goddamn mind!

142
00:12:11,187 --> 00:12:12,229
Put it away.

143
00:12:12,312 --> 00:12:14,562
If Mama catches you, you're in deep shit.

144
00:12:19,354 --> 00:12:21,562
How come Mama keeps a gun anyway?

145
00:12:21,646 --> 00:12:23,812
To protect us from Dad, idiot.

146
00:12:43,521 --> 00:12:46,354
- [Kingsley] Hey, you good?
- [Nolan] Kingsley! Yay!

147
00:12:46,437 --> 00:12:49,146
- [Marvin] Doing well, boys?
- [Nolan] Did you bring me any candy?

148
00:12:49,229 --> 00:12:51,562
- [Kingsley] Of course, sticky hands.
- [woman] Hi, Marvin.

149
00:12:51,646 --> 00:12:52,646
Let's go.

150
00:12:53,312 --> 00:12:54,521
I'm home!

151
00:12:55,979 --> 00:12:57,771
- How are you?
- Mmm-hmm.

152
00:12:58,562 --> 00:13:00,562
- [Marvin] Hey, Mama.
- Hi, sweetie.

153
00:13:00,646 --> 00:13:05,271
I fixed up my friend's motorcycle.
Two hours plus travel, the tools.

154
00:13:05,354 --> 00:13:08,021
- You know.
- And your busted face, that's bonus pay?

155
00:13:08,104 --> 00:13:09,146
'Course not.

156
00:13:09,229 --> 00:13:10,687
Pfft. You know these guys.

157
00:13:10,771 --> 00:13:12,187
They're jealous, that's all.

158
00:13:12,771 --> 00:13:13,687
Ow!

159
00:13:13,771 --> 00:13:15,396
Mama! Let me go!

160
00:13:15,896 --> 00:13:19,854
I already told you I don't want you
showin' up looking like this.

161
00:13:19,937 --> 00:13:22,729
- What did you do this time, Kingsley?
- Nothing, Mama.

162
00:13:22,812 --> 00:13:24,062
I'm not lying.

163
00:13:24,562 --> 00:13:25,729
Ahh.

164
00:13:26,437 --> 00:13:29,062
Cassandra, go make
a healing balm for your brother.

165
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,812
[kids laughing]

166
00:13:34,896 --> 00:13:36,896
[pensive music playing]

167
00:13:46,646 --> 00:13:47,479
What up?

168
00:13:48,062 --> 00:13:49,062
Hey.

169
00:13:51,812 --> 00:13:53,562
Gave some math lessons.

170
00:13:54,146 --> 00:13:58,896
Come here, my boy.
Happy birthday, my darling child.

171
00:14:01,437 --> 00:14:02,812
You like it?

172
00:14:03,896 --> 00:14:05,187
Is it the right size?

173
00:14:05,687 --> 00:14:07,729
You know the significance of the lotus?

174
00:14:09,396 --> 00:14:10,687
Sure I've got the right flower?

175
00:14:12,312 --> 00:14:13,437
We're all sure.

176
00:14:15,562 --> 00:14:16,937
It's you.

177
00:14:22,687 --> 00:14:24,229
Kingsley here yet?

178
00:14:24,312 --> 00:14:26,312
He is. With the kids.

179
00:14:26,937 --> 00:14:29,604
Boom! Heard a loud crack!

180
00:14:29,687 --> 00:14:31,771
- [kids laughing]
- Then I showed him.

181
00:14:31,854 --> 00:14:33,479
I kicked him right in the knee.

182
00:14:33,562 --> 00:14:35,021
Bam! Another crack!

183
00:14:35,104 --> 00:14:38,021
All his bones were snapping.
I kept going, though.

184
00:14:38,104 --> 00:14:41,312
Crack! I broke some legs, broke some arms.

185
00:14:41,396 --> 00:14:42,812
Even punched him in the throat.

186
00:14:42,896 --> 00:14:44,646
And another crack! Right in the jaw!

187
00:14:44,729 --> 00:14:45,896
- Crack!
- [kids] Crack!

188
00:14:45,979 --> 00:14:47,271
- In the chin!
- [kids] Crack!

189
00:14:47,354 --> 00:14:49,271
Gave everything I got.

190
00:14:49,771 --> 00:14:51,021
Hey, what's up, bro?

191
00:14:51,604 --> 00:14:52,771
Who did that?

192
00:14:53,479 --> 00:14:56,312
Ah, forget it.
Just be glad you didn't see their faces.

193
00:14:56,396 --> 00:14:57,687
[laughing]

194
00:15:00,771 --> 00:15:02,854
Appreciate you caring, man.

195
00:15:05,729 --> 00:15:07,646
Then I went straight for his head!

196
00:15:07,729 --> 00:15:09,062
- Crack!
- [all] Crack!

197
00:15:09,146 --> 00:15:12,437
Kylian was always an extra talented boy.

198
00:15:13,104 --> 00:15:16,687
He will go far,
because he is serious, honest, and tough.

199
00:15:17,271 --> 00:15:19,854
He just floats above everyone else.

200
00:15:19,937 --> 00:15:22,854
Just like the lotus flower on murky water.

201
00:15:22,937 --> 00:15:26,937
Follow his example, kids, you hear?
Not Mr. Cock of the Walk over there.

202
00:15:27,021 --> 00:15:29,437
In any case,
where'd you get this cash, King?

203
00:15:29,521 --> 00:15:32,187
- I mean--
- [scoffs] Well, I already told you.

204
00:15:32,896 --> 00:15:34,854
- Whoa, what are you doing?
- Hang on, Mama.

205
00:15:34,937 --> 00:15:37,729
- Knock it off, for real!
- You can't burn up all his money!

206
00:15:37,812 --> 00:15:39,854
Over my dead body
are we eating with drug money.

207
00:15:39,937 --> 00:15:42,604
No, no, no, Mama, I swear.
It's not from drugs, I swear to you.

208
00:15:42,687 --> 00:15:45,479
Anyone here uses drug money,
you're through.

209
00:15:58,312 --> 00:15:59,646
Remember that?

210
00:16:04,396 --> 00:16:06,396
[door creaking open]

211
00:16:08,979 --> 00:16:10,312
[Mama] Annabelle?

212
00:16:13,271 --> 00:16:14,312
This is when you get in?

213
00:16:14,396 --> 00:16:16,479
You might as well
not have come home at all.

214
00:16:16,562 --> 00:16:17,771
Sorry.

215
00:16:18,937 --> 00:16:19,937
That's it?

216
00:16:20,812 --> 00:16:23,021
Come on, Mama.
We were out late last night.

217
00:16:23,104 --> 00:16:24,937
So were they, but they all made it.

218
00:16:29,771 --> 00:16:31,396
Hey, so where's the cake?

219
00:16:31,479 --> 00:16:32,771
[laughs]

220
00:16:33,854 --> 00:16:36,271
Good thing we weren't waiting up for it.

221
00:16:37,396 --> 00:16:39,271
As a mother, you give life to your kids,

222
00:16:39,354 --> 00:16:41,521
and even then they take more and more yet.

223
00:16:41,604 --> 00:16:43,021
What ingrates.

224
00:16:43,104 --> 00:16:44,062
[chuckles softly]

225
00:16:44,146 --> 00:16:46,396
Should've quit
at just two or three ingrates.

226
00:16:46,479 --> 00:16:48,771
- It's overflowing in here.
- [Mama] Mmm-mmm.

227
00:16:50,146 --> 00:16:51,937
This family sitting here?

228
00:16:53,437 --> 00:16:56,604
Ain't nothing in the world
more beautiful than that.

229
00:16:57,562 --> 00:16:58,771
Grab each other's hands.

230
00:16:58,854 --> 00:17:01,562
- [all complaining]
- Take each others hands, now!

231
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:02,729
[Kingsley] Yeah, yeah, yeah.

232
00:17:08,146 --> 00:17:11,146
[gentle music playing]

233
00:17:13,271 --> 00:17:14,937
Do you all feel that?

234
00:17:16,312 --> 00:17:18,187
Going through your arms.

235
00:17:19,854 --> 00:17:21,396
Through your body.

236
00:17:23,187 --> 00:17:24,937
You feel that heat?

237
00:17:27,229 --> 00:17:29,354
Your cheeks warming up.

238
00:17:32,729 --> 00:17:33,854
You feel it?

239
00:17:34,604 --> 00:17:36,562
That's the life force.

240
00:17:37,396 --> 00:17:39,354
Ow, stop squeezing me.

241
00:17:39,979 --> 00:17:41,354
It's the life force.

242
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:47,229
As long as it circulates…
we will be strong.

243
00:17:47,312 --> 00:17:49,229
We'll be protected.

244
00:17:50,187 --> 00:17:52,812
We'll be together, united.

245
00:17:54,354 --> 00:17:56,854
United by this force within us.

246
00:17:56,937 --> 00:17:58,229
That's a Lafleur.

247
00:18:01,229 --> 00:18:02,229
Amen.

248
00:18:02,729 --> 00:18:04,062
[all] Amen.

249
00:18:04,562 --> 00:18:06,562
[rain pattering loudly]

250
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:43,021
[pot clinking softly]

251
00:18:56,729 --> 00:18:58,896
Annabelle? What are you doing?

252
00:19:00,229 --> 00:19:01,771
Nothing, I have a headache.

253
00:19:09,271 --> 00:19:10,604
Are you kidding me?

254
00:19:11,896 --> 00:19:14,271
You think I wouldn't notice
the smell of arada?

255
00:19:16,229 --> 00:19:18,479
You'll vomit all night long.

256
00:19:18,562 --> 00:19:22,229
You'll just make yourself sick,
but it won't stop anything, you got that?

257
00:19:23,187 --> 00:19:25,271
At some point,
you're gonna have to bite the bullet

258
00:19:25,354 --> 00:19:27,604
and take the damn morning-after pill.

259
00:19:27,687 --> 00:19:29,604
That's something we don't mess with.

260
00:19:30,396 --> 00:19:32,312
You know, you're being harsh.

261
00:19:33,687 --> 00:19:35,062
I'm worried.

262
00:19:36,271 --> 00:19:38,354
You're going down the wrong path.

263
00:19:38,437 --> 00:19:39,729
What do you mean?

264
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:42,229
It means you have a lot of problems

265
00:19:42,312 --> 00:19:44,687
and you're counting on me
to fix them for you.

266
00:19:44,771 --> 00:19:46,187
But you're my problem.

267
00:19:46,687 --> 00:19:50,604
You make things worse.
I'd be much better if you let me be.

268
00:19:54,437 --> 00:19:57,437
- I'm going to work.
- [somber music playing]

269
00:20:13,604 --> 00:20:15,271
- [objects clatter]
- [car honking]

270
00:20:15,354 --> 00:20:17,521
- [brakes screeching]
- [loud crash]

271
00:20:21,562 --> 00:20:23,562
[somber music continues]

272
00:20:36,229 --> 00:20:38,229
[phone ringing]

273
00:20:45,396 --> 00:20:47,396
[somber music continues]

274
00:20:49,146 --> 00:20:51,437
[teacher] No? Okay.

275
00:20:52,104 --> 00:20:53,812
Well, don't forget that next week

276
00:20:53,896 --> 00:20:56,312
we're having a test
on modal auxiliary verbs.

277
00:20:56,396 --> 00:20:58,979
I want all of you to succeed.

278
00:20:59,062 --> 00:21:01,479
- Okay? Yes?
- [knock on door]

279
00:21:06,646 --> 00:21:08,646
[somber music building]

280
00:21:23,354 --> 00:21:26,354
- [somber music continues]
- [crying]

281
00:21:38,062 --> 00:21:40,062
[somber music fading]

282
00:21:56,854 --> 00:21:58,396
[knock on door]

283
00:22:05,062 --> 00:22:06,312
[knock on door]

284
00:22:27,896 --> 00:22:29,937
- What are you doing?
- Talking.

285
00:22:30,479 --> 00:22:31,479
About what?

286
00:22:31,562 --> 00:22:32,979
Can we come in?

287
00:22:34,437 --> 00:22:35,771
Go to your rooms and wait.

288
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:37,021
Where's Mama?

289
00:22:39,396 --> 00:22:40,646
Go to your rooms.

290
00:22:40,729 --> 00:22:42,937
- We're hungry.
- We'll eat soon.

291
00:22:54,187 --> 00:22:55,396
[sighs heavily]

292
00:22:57,562 --> 00:22:58,646
Gotta tell them.

293
00:23:02,979 --> 00:23:04,146
Who?

294
00:23:06,562 --> 00:23:07,687
King.

295
00:23:08,979 --> 00:23:10,271
You do it.

296
00:23:20,229 --> 00:23:22,062
- Any of you got some weed?
- [Annabelle] Yeah.

297
00:23:41,104 --> 00:23:43,437
- Want me to tell you a story?
- [kids] Yeah!

298
00:23:55,312 --> 00:23:56,479
And Dark?

299
00:24:01,062 --> 00:24:02,646
We gotta tell Dark.

300
00:24:04,146 --> 00:24:05,896
[Kingsley] All right, guys.

301
00:24:06,854 --> 00:24:11,229
The story I'm gonna tell you all today
is about something not fun.

302
00:24:16,062 --> 00:24:18,646
It's… the story of life.

303
00:24:20,646 --> 00:24:22,312
When life gets bad.

304
00:24:25,104 --> 00:24:27,104
[line ringing]

305
00:24:33,187 --> 00:24:36,354
[on voicemail] You've reached Nathanaël.
Leave a message and shut up already.

306
00:24:36,437 --> 00:24:38,687
- [voicemail beeps]
- Call me back, yeah?

307
00:24:52,271 --> 00:24:53,562
[knock on door]

308
00:25:00,479 --> 00:25:03,479
[mournful music playing]

309
00:25:33,771 --> 00:25:36,354
[mournful music swells and fades]

310
00:25:59,312 --> 00:26:02,104
[man] We've got room at home for the kids,
you know.

311
00:26:02,187 --> 00:26:03,521
That's why we came.

312
00:26:04,271 --> 00:26:06,604
It'd be good for them to be spoiled a bit.

313
00:26:07,854 --> 00:26:09,729
Don't worry. We got this.

314
00:26:10,312 --> 00:26:12,062
It's too much for you alone.

315
00:26:13,937 --> 00:26:15,687
After that allowance check.

316
00:26:16,354 --> 00:26:19,104
[woman] You'll have to kill me
before they get the kids.

317
00:26:46,396 --> 00:26:47,396
Dark.

318
00:26:58,687 --> 00:27:00,021
[breathes deeply]

319
00:27:15,521 --> 00:27:17,312
You all chose to put her there?

320
00:27:17,979 --> 00:27:19,646
We didn't have a choice, bro.

321
00:27:19,729 --> 00:27:21,229
Just be happy she has a spot.

322
00:27:25,396 --> 00:27:28,354
So Mama would rather join the dead
than forgive the living.

323
00:27:32,646 --> 00:27:34,937
No way. I'm not forgiven.

324
00:27:40,146 --> 00:27:41,062
[spits]

325
00:27:46,771 --> 00:27:49,771
[woman] Would you like to come
back to the house for a bite to eat?

326
00:27:49,854 --> 00:27:51,854
[indistinct chatter]

327
00:27:52,396 --> 00:27:54,229
We'll bring them straight home.

328
00:27:58,812 --> 00:28:00,896
It's okay, Auntie.
We're fine with the bus.

329
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:02,146
No biggie.

330
00:28:02,229 --> 00:28:03,229
Let's go.

331
00:28:04,896 --> 00:28:07,687
You won't be able
to take care of them on your own.

332
00:28:09,604 --> 00:28:11,771
Marvin, children need stability.

333
00:28:11,854 --> 00:28:15,146
- Hey! We're fine with the bus, we said.
- It's better if they're with us.

334
00:28:16,646 --> 00:28:18,187
Give us a few days, all right?

335
00:28:21,312 --> 00:28:23,146
That one's a real witch.

336
00:28:23,229 --> 00:28:24,229
Let's go.

337
00:28:25,937 --> 00:28:26,979
Come on.

338
00:28:40,979 --> 00:28:42,896
Find me a dock worker.

339
00:28:43,812 --> 00:28:44,812
Seriously?

340
00:28:46,312 --> 00:28:48,271
We're moving to phase three.

341
00:28:48,354 --> 00:28:50,937
[intriguing music playing]

342
00:29:15,979 --> 00:29:18,521
Are you Milord? Thought you'd be older.

343
00:29:19,271 --> 00:29:20,979
Are you Jean-Claude?

344
00:29:21,062 --> 00:29:22,646
Just call me JC, man.

345
00:29:22,729 --> 00:29:25,562
JC. That's fine.

346
00:29:26,104 --> 00:29:27,104
Okay.

347
00:29:27,187 --> 00:29:28,354
The basic rundown.

348
00:29:28,979 --> 00:29:31,437
I know who you sell to,
and who sells to you.

349
00:29:33,187 --> 00:29:34,479
I can see…

350
00:29:34,562 --> 00:29:37,562
you ain't got no chains, no jewelry.

351
00:29:37,646 --> 00:29:38,896
Dressed casual.

352
00:29:40,104 --> 00:29:41,604
Incognito mode.

353
00:29:43,104 --> 00:29:44,104
That's good.

354
00:29:45,271 --> 00:29:46,479
That's how I roll.

355
00:29:47,396 --> 00:29:48,437
And you?

356
00:29:48,937 --> 00:29:50,187
What's your deal?

357
00:29:52,979 --> 00:29:55,396
Nobody above and nobody underneath.

358
00:29:56,104 --> 00:29:57,146
Like Putin.

359
00:29:57,646 --> 00:29:58,687
[chuckles]

360
00:29:59,812 --> 00:30:01,771
Still got a long way to go, buddy.

361
00:30:03,104 --> 00:30:04,187
Phase one.

362
00:30:04,854 --> 00:30:06,896
Sell locally. I got it.

363
00:30:07,396 --> 00:30:10,896
Phase two.
Homemade goods traded all over France.

364
00:30:10,979 --> 00:30:12,312
Mules and shit.

365
00:30:12,396 --> 00:30:14,812
That's for them idiots
who wanna get caught.

366
00:30:14,896 --> 00:30:17,312
Phase three. Exports on a larger scale.

367
00:30:17,812 --> 00:30:18,937
That's what I'm after.

368
00:30:19,646 --> 00:30:22,562
Okay. You're ambitious.

369
00:30:23,229 --> 00:30:26,646
Top-notch reputation, but you need more.

370
00:30:27,771 --> 00:30:29,187
From this point on…

371
00:30:29,771 --> 00:30:31,562
I've got my eyes on you.

372
00:30:31,646 --> 00:30:33,187
Nothing gets past me.

373
00:30:33,271 --> 00:30:36,146
I've got eyes, in town, in the city.

374
00:30:36,229 --> 00:30:38,479
You won't be able to fart
without me knowing what you ate.

375
00:30:38,562 --> 00:30:39,562
Got it?

376
00:30:40,479 --> 00:30:42,062
Not a peep about you.

377
00:30:42,146 --> 00:30:44,479
Not from the cops, or your little buddies.

378
00:30:44,979 --> 00:30:47,771
I'm not about risks,
so you better stay invisible.

379
00:30:47,854 --> 00:30:49,687
Milord is invisible.

380
00:30:50,312 --> 00:30:51,687
Knock off the nickname.

381
00:30:52,604 --> 00:30:54,312
I want your real name.

382
00:30:55,229 --> 00:30:56,812
Unlock your phone and give it to me.

383
00:30:58,896 --> 00:30:59,896
What is it?

384
00:31:00,812 --> 00:31:02,937
My family has got nothing to do with this.

385
00:31:03,021 --> 00:31:04,979
What, you think we gonna torture them?

386
00:31:05,979 --> 00:31:07,771
No one gets in bed with an alias.

387
00:31:09,062 --> 00:31:12,062
["BB Compte (feat. Akiyo)"
by Meryl playing]

388
00:31:25,146 --> 00:31:28,146
Uh, 230 for water.

389
00:31:28,229 --> 00:31:30,312
We got one month to settle it.

390
00:31:30,812 --> 00:31:33,604
We're two months behind
on the scooter's insurance.

391
00:31:33,687 --> 00:31:36,771
- [Marvin] How much is that?
- Uh, 55 euros.

392
00:31:39,937 --> 00:31:41,062
[clicks tongue] Damn.

393
00:31:43,979 --> 00:31:47,187
That's the third late notice.
They've reduced our power.

394
00:31:48,146 --> 00:31:51,521
I turned on the microwave
to reheat the muffins from yesterday.

395
00:31:51,604 --> 00:31:52,687
[sighs]

396
00:31:53,396 --> 00:31:56,021
[Marvin] We've got just enough
to keep the fridge on.

397
00:31:57,187 --> 00:31:58,687
How much do we owe?

398
00:31:59,396 --> 00:32:03,562
Mmm, 314, including the late fees.

399
00:32:03,646 --> 00:32:07,271
And the home insurance is 102.89.

400
00:32:08,604 --> 00:32:10,021
And the groceries too.

401
00:32:11,187 --> 00:32:12,937
Mama was paying for all this?

402
00:32:13,521 --> 00:32:14,812
How'd she manage?

403
00:32:15,562 --> 00:32:19,604
She had her stand.
As well as the services, the allowance…

404
00:32:19,687 --> 00:32:25,021
You know what the last thing
I said to her was? "Let me be."

405
00:32:26,604 --> 00:32:29,187
"I'd be better off if you'd let me be."

406
00:32:35,146 --> 00:32:36,312
[crying]

407
00:32:53,479 --> 00:32:55,479
[darkly intriguing music playing]

408
00:33:20,771 --> 00:33:23,771
- We can't make it without Auntie.
- [woman] Oh hell no.

409
00:33:23,854 --> 00:33:25,521
Auntie? No way.

410
00:33:25,604 --> 00:33:27,146
What do you propose?

411
00:33:27,229 --> 00:33:31,854
Well, um, Cassandra
could run the stand on the weekends.

412
00:33:31,937 --> 00:33:34,604
I'll go back to work at Burger King.

413
00:33:36,062 --> 00:33:37,687
And how do much you make?

414
00:33:37,771 --> 00:33:39,854
- 1,600?
- Yeah, barely.

415
00:33:41,271 --> 00:33:43,729
What about me? What should I do?

416
00:33:43,812 --> 00:33:48,646
Annabelle, you gotta get your diploma.
No way you're dropping out again, come on.

417
00:33:48,729 --> 00:33:49,896
Okay.

418
00:33:52,854 --> 00:33:53,687
And you, Kiki?

419
00:33:54,562 --> 00:33:55,729
What do you suggest?

420
00:33:55,812 --> 00:33:58,521
Uh, I have no idea.

421
00:33:58,604 --> 00:34:00,854
I can do some tutoring after school.

422
00:34:03,271 --> 00:34:05,521
With these numbers,
without Auntie, it's impossible.

423
00:34:05,604 --> 00:34:08,146
Okay, stop, stop.
You're giving me a headache.

424
00:34:08,646 --> 00:34:11,062
No one's gonna pay,
not Belle, nor you, Marvin.

425
00:34:12,979 --> 00:34:14,771
I'll tell you what we're gonna do.

426
00:34:16,646 --> 00:34:19,229
We won't end up on the streets
if we know how to work 'em.

427
00:34:19,937 --> 00:34:21,187
What does that mean?

428
00:34:21,687 --> 00:34:23,271
Let me deal with it.

429
00:34:23,354 --> 00:34:25,437
- Do you trust me?
- No.

430
00:34:26,312 --> 00:34:29,729
- The street won't put food on the table.
- It will more than potted plants, Marvin.

431
00:34:30,312 --> 00:34:34,104
King, you've lost it. For real, though.

432
00:34:34,771 --> 00:34:36,812
Mama didn't want us touching that shit.

433
00:34:37,521 --> 00:34:40,187
- So don't touch it.
- Drugs isn't how this family does things.

434
00:34:40,271 --> 00:34:41,979
And having a dead Mom is?

435
00:34:43,396 --> 00:34:45,312
You got a better idea? I'm all ears.

436
00:34:45,396 --> 00:34:48,396
Till then, I'm an adult.
I can do what I want.

437
00:34:59,437 --> 00:35:01,646
Are we gonna live with Auntie?

438
00:35:01,729 --> 00:35:03,896
[Kingsley] No. Go to sleep.

439
00:35:03,979 --> 00:35:05,979
[gentle music playing]

440
00:36:23,812 --> 00:36:27,437
- ["Bien sûr" by Jkevlar playing]
- Okay! The beast is loose!

441
00:36:29,729 --> 00:36:31,479
Okay!

442
00:36:32,979 --> 00:36:35,646
El SherKhan, rolling up!

443
00:36:37,896 --> 00:36:40,104
Yo! How are you, man?

444
00:36:40,854 --> 00:36:42,937
- You all good, bro?
- Yeah, dawg. All good.

445
00:36:44,437 --> 00:36:45,271
You know it.

446
00:36:47,479 --> 00:36:48,854
You know it, son.

447
00:36:48,937 --> 00:36:50,771
Look at you, all thinned out.

448
00:36:50,854 --> 00:36:52,396
- 'Sup, dawg?
- Damn.

449
00:36:52,479 --> 00:36:53,354
Yeah, you got skinny.

450
00:36:53,437 --> 00:36:56,979
I leaned out.
I'm built for speed like a cheetah.

451
00:36:57,479 --> 00:37:01,021
[laughing] Yo, is that some new bling too?

452
00:37:01,812 --> 00:37:04,562
- Asked for gold, but they ain't have any.
- [man laughing]

453
00:37:04,646 --> 00:37:07,312
- Here, cousin.
- Hell yeah, my cousin. You get it.

454
00:37:07,896 --> 00:37:09,812
[man] You'll see, we went all out.

455
00:37:10,312 --> 00:37:14,187
[man] Damn, bro. It's good to see you.
For real, son. We gonna party.

456
00:37:14,271 --> 00:37:16,354
- [SherKhan] Damn straight.
- [man] Let's go, guy.

457
00:37:16,437 --> 00:37:19,437
- [rap song continues]
- [indistinct background chatter]

458
00:37:38,979 --> 00:37:40,479
Ooh, this is bad!

459
00:37:41,687 --> 00:37:43,312
Welcome back, dude.

460
00:37:43,396 --> 00:37:46,562
- Gotta show respect.
- So business is moving up, huh?

461
00:37:46,646 --> 00:37:49,604
Damn straight, it's all going great.
We get shit done.

462
00:37:49,687 --> 00:37:51,854
Hell yeah, seems like it.

463
00:37:54,021 --> 00:37:56,562
Damn good. It's going great without me.

464
00:37:57,937 --> 00:37:59,021
Just doing our best.

465
00:37:59,604 --> 00:38:00,979
Your best is a lot, Vince.

466
00:38:01,062 --> 00:38:03,187
That's what I like about you.

467
00:38:04,396 --> 00:38:05,271
Champagne.

468
00:38:05,354 --> 00:38:08,146
Hell yeah, the cousin's out! Hell yeah.

469
00:38:08,729 --> 00:38:10,521
- [bottle thuds]
- [Vincez] Oh!

470
00:38:11,104 --> 00:38:13,104
- [bottle thudding]
- Ahh! Stop!

471
00:38:13,187 --> 00:38:15,229
[groaning]

472
00:38:16,479 --> 00:38:19,146
You really thought you could
skim off my business and not get caught?

473
00:38:19,229 --> 00:38:22,437
SherKhan, stop, man.
Vincez wanted to surprise you.

474
00:38:22,521 --> 00:38:24,104
He kept it all, look.

475
00:38:27,729 --> 00:38:29,104
[woman] You're late.

476
00:38:29,604 --> 00:38:30,896
Yeah, I know, sorry.

477
00:38:31,687 --> 00:38:34,979
But look what I picked up.
Smells burnt, though.

478
00:38:40,479 --> 00:38:41,979
What's wrong, sweetheart?

479
00:38:42,062 --> 00:38:43,437
Look at her feet.

480
00:38:50,854 --> 00:38:55,104
Look at this. Thaïs has been wearing shoes
that don't fit her for weeks now.

481
00:38:55,187 --> 00:38:56,604
She didn't tell us, no one noticed.

482
00:38:56,687 --> 00:38:59,729
And that's nothing compared
to everything Mama did for us.

483
00:39:00,229 --> 00:39:01,229
Have you guys looked in--

484
00:39:01,312 --> 00:39:04,354
The only ones that don't have holes
are Marvin's old SpongeBob socks,

485
00:39:04,437 --> 00:39:05,687
but she won't wear them.

486
00:39:06,979 --> 00:39:08,104
Go to sleep, princess.

487
00:39:08,187 --> 00:39:09,354
Be right there.

488
00:39:26,146 --> 00:39:28,229
We can't make it like this, King.

489
00:39:28,854 --> 00:39:30,062
We won't manage.

490
00:39:30,979 --> 00:39:34,146
Cassandra and I gotta stay up all night
to finish our homework.

491
00:39:34,771 --> 00:39:37,979
I know it's a lot. We are in deep shit.

492
00:39:40,146 --> 00:39:42,646
But we're gonna get out of it, hmm?

493
00:39:43,312 --> 00:39:44,562
I know what to do.

494
00:39:46,312 --> 00:39:47,937
I know how to make us money.

495
00:39:48,771 --> 00:39:50,146
I swear to you.

496
00:39:51,896 --> 00:39:55,062
FOR SALE

497
00:39:57,479 --> 00:39:59,729
CALLING MARV

498
00:40:02,521 --> 00:40:04,062
Yo, why did you do that?

499
00:40:04,146 --> 00:40:06,979
The drone doesn't belong to you, dude.
Show some respect, man!

500
00:40:07,479 --> 00:40:09,104
Kiki asked me to sell it.

501
00:40:09,187 --> 00:40:11,271
- It'll pay the electricity bill.
- [clicks tongue]

502
00:40:13,146 --> 00:40:15,854
- [Vincez] Yo, is King here?
- Yeah, over there.

503
00:40:15,937 --> 00:40:17,104
Okay, thanks.

504
00:40:21,479 --> 00:40:24,229
Yo. I'm sorry about your mother.

505
00:40:25,187 --> 00:40:27,146
Mine used to buy herbs from her.

506
00:40:29,979 --> 00:40:31,271
Looking for your next play?

507
00:40:33,104 --> 00:40:34,229
Who did that?

508
00:40:34,937 --> 00:40:35,771
My cousin.

509
00:40:37,146 --> 00:40:38,937
SherKhan, man. [clicks tongue]

510
00:40:40,396 --> 00:40:42,729
He'll have to pay and he's good for it.

511
00:40:43,312 --> 00:40:44,229
Mmm-hmm.

512
00:40:44,312 --> 00:40:45,604
What's the plan?

513
00:40:45,687 --> 00:40:47,646
I know where he hides his dope at.

514
00:40:49,437 --> 00:40:51,437
[expectant music playing softly]

515
00:40:57,021 --> 00:40:58,062
No.

516
00:40:59,021 --> 00:41:02,521
[Kingsley] You won't have to do anything.
Just drop me off, I do my thing.

517
00:41:02,604 --> 00:41:04,479
It'll take ten minutes, tops,
and we're flush.

518
00:41:04,562 --> 00:41:05,437
No!

519
00:41:05,521 --> 00:41:07,687
[sighs] You don't want to help me,
for real?

520
00:41:07,771 --> 00:41:10,062
No, I don't want to help you. No.

521
00:41:10,146 --> 00:41:12,854
You're gonna fuck shit up.
You'll fuck it up for all of us.

522
00:41:12,937 --> 00:41:14,187
Man, this is-- [clicks tongue]

523
00:41:14,271 --> 00:41:16,146
Whatever, man. It's fine.

524
00:41:19,312 --> 00:41:22,062
- Marv said you were up to something.
- You in?

525
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:26,229
- Robbing someone again?
- What do you mean? I didn't rob no one.

526
00:41:27,229 --> 00:41:28,479
Don't worry 'bout it.

527
00:41:28,562 --> 00:41:30,521
This Milord is gonna
have to watch his back.

528
00:41:30,604 --> 00:41:32,062
I'mma show him what's what.

529
00:41:32,562 --> 00:41:33,812
But forget that.

530
00:41:34,562 --> 00:41:35,937
You're making enemies, bro.

531
00:41:36,021 --> 00:41:37,021
So what?

532
00:41:37,646 --> 00:41:41,062
Well, those enemies
could go after the family.

533
00:41:41,562 --> 00:41:44,687
That's beside the point.
I need to know if I can count on you.

534
00:41:45,604 --> 00:41:48,854
No. I'm sorry, it's a bad idea.

535
00:41:49,687 --> 00:41:52,229
Man, where do you get off
judging my ideas?

536
00:41:52,896 --> 00:41:54,021
[clicks tongue]

537
00:41:54,104 --> 00:41:56,479
Voice of purity over here. God damn.

538
00:42:02,812 --> 00:42:04,021
JC
YOUR BROTHER KINGSLEY…

539
00:42:05,354 --> 00:42:09,562
YOUR BROTHER KINGSLEY WORRIES ME.
YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE FOR HIM.

540
00:42:09,646 --> 00:42:11,646
[sighs and clicks tongue]

541
00:42:13,562 --> 00:42:15,562
[dog barking faintly]

542
00:42:18,312 --> 00:42:20,854
[commentator on TV] So much excitement
happening here tonight.

543
00:42:20,937 --> 00:42:24,812
And another missed goal by Martinique.
The fans are not happy.

544
00:42:25,479 --> 00:42:28,479
[TV continues indistinctly in background]

545
00:42:40,937 --> 00:42:41,854
Hey.

546
00:42:43,312 --> 00:42:44,312
See that bar over there?

547
00:42:45,687 --> 00:42:47,187
Keep an eye out, okay?

548
00:42:47,687 --> 00:42:50,771
You see him come out of that bar,
and walk down this way,

549
00:42:50,854 --> 00:42:52,729
call me immediately, okay?

550
00:42:53,771 --> 00:42:55,646
So how will we know which one?

551
00:42:55,729 --> 00:42:59,229
He's got two big chains
and a monitor around his ankle.

552
00:42:59,312 --> 00:43:00,146
You'll see it.

553
00:43:00,229 --> 00:43:03,354
So if we see him walk by us,
we'll call you?

554
00:43:04,146 --> 00:43:04,979
Yep.

555
00:43:05,646 --> 00:43:07,521
He won't be out for a minute.
There's a game on.

556
00:43:07,604 --> 00:43:11,729
In 20 minutes, I'll message you,
tell you it's over, and you can peace out.

557
00:43:11,812 --> 00:43:12,646
- Okay.
- Okay?

558
00:43:12,729 --> 00:43:14,271
- Yeah.
- All right, kids.

559
00:43:14,354 --> 00:43:15,479
You got this.

560
00:43:15,562 --> 00:43:17,104
Don't do anything dumb.

561
00:43:21,229 --> 00:43:22,229
King?

562
00:43:22,312 --> 00:43:23,437
Hmm? Yeah?

563
00:43:24,604 --> 00:43:25,771
If he sees us?

564
00:43:26,271 --> 00:43:29,271
Well, so what if he sees you?

565
00:43:29,354 --> 00:43:31,187
Just a girl and some kids, that's all.

566
00:43:32,437 --> 00:43:33,771
Whatcha think he's gonna do?

567
00:43:35,021 --> 00:43:38,021
Just don't look him in the eye.
And tell them not to look at him either.

568
00:43:38,604 --> 00:43:39,646
Okay.

569
00:43:39,729 --> 00:43:42,479
[suspenseful music playing]

570
00:43:42,562 --> 00:43:44,854
[commentator on TV] They've withstood
the Lillois offense.

571
00:43:45,437 --> 00:43:48,479
Though poor Martinique
is still trailing three-zero.

572
00:43:48,562 --> 00:43:52,437
In the second half of the French Cup final
and it's been an ordeal for them.

573
00:43:52,521 --> 00:43:54,896
The Docks are
monopolizing the ball yet again.

574
00:43:54,979 --> 00:43:58,354
Lille, on the attack,
are they gonna score another goal?

575
00:43:58,437 --> 00:44:00,812
It doesn't look like Martinique
has what it takes today.

576
00:44:00,896 --> 00:44:03,146
- Oh! And Lille scores!
- Come on, ref! What you doing?

577
00:44:03,229 --> 00:44:05,771
Bringing their total to four
against Martinique's zero.

578
00:44:05,854 --> 00:44:07,437
At this point, any chance of Martinique…

579
00:44:07,521 --> 00:44:10,229
[suspenseful music playing]

580
00:44:28,437 --> 00:44:29,687
[Kingsley] It's me.

581
00:44:43,521 --> 00:44:45,354
- Who's this?
- It's my brother.

582
00:44:45,854 --> 00:44:47,062
Okay.

583
00:44:47,604 --> 00:44:49,437
- Got eyes on my cousin?
- Of course, son.

584
00:44:49,521 --> 00:44:51,896
Come on, where is it? We've gotta go.

585
00:44:52,646 --> 00:44:53,854
Over there.

586
00:44:55,521 --> 00:44:58,187
[commentator continues] Fans are growing
increasingly frustrated

587
00:44:58,271 --> 00:44:59,896
with this embarrassing performance.

588
00:44:59,979 --> 00:45:02,771
Can Lille bring their goal count to five
before halftime?

589
00:45:02,854 --> 00:45:04,021
Lille was on fire tonight…

590
00:45:04,104 --> 00:45:08,021
- [men grumbling]
- They're playing like bitch-ass amateurs.

591
00:45:08,104 --> 00:45:10,604
Fans are surely baffled
with Martinique's pitiful playing tonight.

592
00:45:10,687 --> 00:45:12,729
We can see fights breaking out.
Look at this.

593
00:45:12,812 --> 00:45:14,479
You bring your family…

594
00:45:16,896 --> 00:45:18,062
Hey.

595
00:45:18,146 --> 00:45:21,479
[suspenseful music continues]

596
00:45:27,771 --> 00:45:29,562
He's got a chain.

597
00:45:34,521 --> 00:45:36,437
He's getting closer.

598
00:45:41,104 --> 00:45:42,687
Sick of this damn team!

599
00:45:44,354 --> 00:45:45,854
Doesn't have a monitor.

600
00:45:45,937 --> 00:45:48,646
[indistinct chatter]

601
00:45:52,062 --> 00:45:54,562
Okay. Keep looking. Next.

602
00:45:54,646 --> 00:45:58,396
[man in background] I gotta decompress.
I can't sit and watch a game like that.

603
00:45:58,479 --> 00:46:00,812
[suspenseful music continues]

604
00:46:14,979 --> 00:46:16,562
How many are there?

605
00:46:29,271 --> 00:46:32,062
[commentator] Martinique
regains possession of the ball.

606
00:46:32,146 --> 00:46:34,021
Maybe they're starting to wake back up.

607
00:46:34,104 --> 00:46:36,146
We can certainly see panic is setting in…

608
00:46:36,229 --> 00:46:39,437
- [fans clamoring]
- No, they're finished. It's stupid.

609
00:46:39,521 --> 00:46:41,937
Not yet. One half still left.

610
00:46:42,437 --> 00:46:45,271
Even with four half-times,
there's still no way they'll make it up.

611
00:46:45,354 --> 00:46:46,896
[clicks tongue] Come on, man.

612
00:46:47,479 --> 00:46:49,396
[commentator]
…at this point will not happen.

613
00:46:49,479 --> 00:46:51,812
There's no way
they're gonna be able to come back…

614
00:46:52,396 --> 00:46:54,479
[suspenseful music continues]

615
00:47:28,812 --> 00:47:30,271
Is that him?

616
00:47:31,771 --> 00:47:32,812
Could be.

617
00:47:32,896 --> 00:47:34,312
Don't look at him.

618
00:47:40,271 --> 00:47:43,229
I'm peacing out, dawg. This is bullshit.

619
00:47:43,312 --> 00:47:44,354
[man] Where you going?

620
00:47:44,437 --> 00:47:47,271
To Bel'hair. Damn messed-up my night.

621
00:47:51,396 --> 00:47:53,396
[suspenseful music continues]

622
00:47:58,437 --> 00:48:00,896
- That's all.
- More than I expected.

623
00:48:01,396 --> 00:48:03,687
Leo, go look under the seat,
should be bigger bags in there.

624
00:48:10,229 --> 00:48:11,229
Well?

625
00:48:15,396 --> 00:48:16,479
Yeah.

626
00:48:22,146 --> 00:48:24,729
[suspenseful music continues]

627
00:48:37,396 --> 00:48:38,646
Yo, help me.

628
00:48:38,729 --> 00:48:40,479
- Pick up, King.
- [line ringing]

629
00:48:56,271 --> 00:48:59,812
Normally when you invite a girl over,
you gotta leave the door open, right?

630
00:48:59,896 --> 00:49:01,937
- You want it open?
- [girl laughs]

631
00:49:02,021 --> 00:49:03,146
No, I'm kidding.

632
00:49:07,312 --> 00:49:10,271
[laughs] You wanna be Tony Montana?

633
00:49:16,437 --> 00:49:18,229
No. He's a loser.

634
00:49:18,312 --> 00:49:21,146
I'm sorry? How come?

635
00:49:22,312 --> 00:49:24,479
Because he always made bad choices.

636
00:49:24,562 --> 00:49:26,812
He's a show-off, he's impulsive.

637
00:49:28,979 --> 00:49:30,812
Why have a poster of him then?

638
00:49:35,854 --> 00:49:38,312
A reminder to not end up like him.

639
00:49:44,604 --> 00:49:46,604
[suspenseful music continues]

640
00:49:53,562 --> 00:49:56,146
Can't carry all these on a scooter.
You got a car here?

641
00:49:56,229 --> 00:50:00,021
[clicks tongue] Seriously,
ain't you prepared at all, dude? [sighs]

642
00:50:01,479 --> 00:50:02,646
Damn it.

643
00:50:06,146 --> 00:50:07,729
- [line ringing]
- [Ambre] Hello?

644
00:50:07,812 --> 00:50:09,604
- Ambre?
- Yeah.

645
00:50:10,271 --> 00:50:11,687
We're in deep shit.

646
00:50:14,396 --> 00:50:16,187
Kylian, gotta talk to you.

647
00:50:18,562 --> 00:50:20,812
Kingsley's about to do something stupid.

648
00:50:26,229 --> 00:50:28,104
He took the stash
of some guy named SherKhan,

649
00:50:28,187 --> 00:50:29,479
and that guy's on his way back.

650
00:50:30,562 --> 00:50:32,354
- SherKhan?
- You know him?

651
00:50:33,562 --> 00:50:34,687
I've heard the name before.

652
00:50:34,771 --> 00:50:36,896
Well, he's about to get his ass busted.

653
00:50:37,396 --> 00:50:40,229
- And Marvin?
- Can't reach him. Kingsley, neither.

654
00:50:40,312 --> 00:50:42,979
Fine.
Go back to your room, I'll call Fatso.

655
00:50:43,062 --> 00:50:45,146
His brother's connected.
It could help out.

656
00:50:45,229 --> 00:50:46,354
That's the most I can do.

657
00:50:47,562 --> 00:50:49,062
God damn.

658
00:50:53,187 --> 00:50:55,437
[suspenseful music continues]

659
00:50:55,521 --> 00:50:58,146
Oh, come on.
Damn, you got any tape or shit?

660
00:50:58,896 --> 00:51:02,604
Man, for real,
you guys are pissing me off! [exhales]

661
00:51:15,354 --> 00:51:18,354
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [phone vibrating]

662
00:51:21,354 --> 00:51:22,521
Yeah, baby, what's going on?

663
00:51:22,604 --> 00:51:25,437
- There's someone here.
- What? Who?

664
00:51:25,521 --> 00:51:27,729
I don't know, they're in the living room.
I can hear them.

665
00:51:27,812 --> 00:51:30,021
- Hmm?
- I locked myself in the bedroom.

666
00:51:30,104 --> 00:51:31,437
Damn it, what do I do?

667
00:51:32,312 --> 00:51:33,937
Who are these guys?

668
00:51:34,979 --> 00:51:36,479
Tell 'em I'm coming! Tell 'em!

669
00:51:36,562 --> 00:51:38,729
Yo, some guys are at Coco's!

670
00:51:40,104 --> 00:51:41,521
My man is coming!

671
00:51:41,604 --> 00:51:44,937
Yeah, SherKhan is coming!
He finds you here, he'll kill you!

672
00:51:45,979 --> 00:51:49,354
- [man] He's coming now?
- Right now! And he's gonna kill you!

673
00:51:50,479 --> 00:51:51,354
You sure?

674
00:51:51,437 --> 00:51:54,062
Oh, you will find out
soon enough, assholes!

675
00:51:56,604 --> 00:51:58,604
[suspenseful music continues]

676
00:52:02,604 --> 00:52:04,562
CALL FROM SK

677
00:52:05,646 --> 00:52:07,687
- It's my cousin.
- Let us out.

678
00:52:09,396 --> 00:52:10,771
[SherKhan] Go to Bel'hair!

679
00:52:11,437 --> 00:52:13,146
- Huh?
- Go to the salon! Now!

680
00:52:13,729 --> 00:52:14,937
Right now?

681
00:52:15,437 --> 00:52:19,271
Yeah, I was gonna go, but I can't.
You go, tell me if everything's okay.

682
00:52:19,812 --> 00:52:20,812
I'll be there in 20.

683
00:52:20,896 --> 00:52:23,604
- Yeah, sure, but is there a reason?
- Just go! God damn!

684
00:52:27,146 --> 00:52:28,146
Come on, open it.

685
00:52:29,312 --> 00:52:31,646
He wants me to check out the salon.
Something's off.

686
00:52:31,729 --> 00:52:33,604
And so what? Let us out!

687
00:52:35,854 --> 00:52:37,604
What are you doing?

688
00:52:37,687 --> 00:52:38,979
You gonna let us out?

689
00:52:40,396 --> 00:52:41,604
[clicks tongue]

690
00:52:42,229 --> 00:52:43,312
Hey, get off me!

691
00:52:43,396 --> 00:52:45,896
- [dramatic music playing]
- Look at you!

692
00:52:49,479 --> 00:52:51,646
- Give me the key!
- Get off!

693
00:52:54,187 --> 00:52:57,479
- Get off! Get off me, asshole!
- [dramatic music continues]

694
00:52:58,187 --> 00:52:59,896
[both grunting]

695
00:53:05,979 --> 00:53:06,854
Ahh!

696
00:53:06,937 --> 00:53:09,937
- [groaning]
- [dramatic music continues]

697
00:53:11,937 --> 00:53:14,771
- [slicing]
- [groaning]

698
00:53:14,854 --> 00:53:16,271
[gun fires]

699
00:53:17,271 --> 00:53:19,271
[both groaning]

700
00:53:22,104 --> 00:53:24,687
- [music fading]
- [Vincez groaning and whimpering]

701
00:53:50,021 --> 00:53:52,021
[door rattling]

702
00:53:59,062 --> 00:54:01,604
[Vincez groaning]

703
00:54:04,479 --> 00:54:06,437
- Let's go, let's go.
- [groaning continues]

704
00:54:06,521 --> 00:54:07,646
[gun clatters]

705
00:54:24,312 --> 00:54:27,104
[Thaïs] That was so cool.
I hope we do it again soon.

706
00:54:27,979 --> 00:54:29,312
Annabelle?

707
00:54:29,396 --> 00:54:32,312
Let's tell Kingsley,
so he'll use us again.

708
00:54:34,229 --> 00:54:35,604
Annabelle?

709
00:54:36,396 --> 00:54:37,396
We're really tough!

710
00:54:37,479 --> 00:54:40,479
["Bienvenue aux antilles"
by Jozii playing on headphones]

711
00:54:54,854 --> 00:54:57,854
["Bienvenue aux antilles"
continues playing]

712
00:55:13,896 --> 00:55:16,687
YOUR BROTHER KINGSLEY WORRIES ME.
YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE FOR HIM.

713
00:55:34,604 --> 00:55:37,271
IN MEMORY OF LIONEL LEPAGE

714
00:55:37,354 --> 00:55:39,354
["Bienvenue aux antilles"
by Jozii continues playing]
